Rating: 4
Did a test run of the recipe as written. It was good, but I wanted more flavor, more veggies, and less fat. Made a second batch, using the recipe as a guide. My version: Roasted and peeled 2 red peppers. Sauteéd them in olive oil with slices of 2 fresh red onions and their greens. Added a hefty amount of fresh Greek oregano. Used challah, Irish cheddar and goat cheese. Substituted one cup of milk with Trader Joe's Roasted Red Pepper and Tomato soup (thanks to a Chowhound poster) and used fat-free milk. Doubled the Dijon. It was both visually appealing and delicious.

Rating: 4
This was a hit at my brunch on Saturday. Even my picky husband said it was really good. I used an 11x17 inch casserole dish so I added 1 slice of bread, 1 egg, 1/4 cup milk. I chopped 3 med/small red bell peppers and 1 teaspoon each of salt and pepper. It must sit at least 6 hours before baking. I made it at 6 am and put it in the oven at noon.

